# Task: [REDO] File upload with camera, progress, and conflicts

## Description

PREVIOUS JOB (job-013) FAILED - no upload functionality was created at all.

Steps:
1. Create src/lib/upload.ts - Upload manager:
   - Chunked upload support for large files
   - Progress tracking per file
   - Queue management (max concurrent uploads)
   - Retry on failure
2. Create src/components/files/UploadButton.tsx - Upload trigger:
   - File picker (multiple files)
   - Camera capture option (accept='image/*' with capture)
   - Folder upload on supported browsers
3. Create src/components/files/UploadProgressSheet.tsx - Progress display:
   - List of uploading files with progress bars
   - Cancel individual or all uploads
   - Show completed/failed status
4. Create src/components/files/UploadConflictDialog.tsx - Conflict resolution:
   - When filename already exists: replace, rename, or skip
   - Apply to all option for batch uploads
5. Create src/components/files/NewFolderDialog.tsx - Create new folder
6. Create src/components/files/NewFileDialog.tsx - Create new empty file (markdown, text)
7. Wire UploadButton into FileBrowser FAB actions
8. Create tests for UploadButton and upload.ts
9. Run npm test to verify

Context: Redo of job-013-file-upload. File browser exists at src/components/files/FileBrowser.tsx.

## Files to Modify

- src/components/files/FileBrowser.tsx
- src/lib/api.ts

